name: Tim Quast
tweet: @iamjoesrage @EdgeStructure JR, I think it's more pedestrian.  Market makers are exempt from short-locate rules. They create shares to fill a raft of retail limit orders. When stop-losses start to pile up, they vanish. Quotes crumble. Stock gets halted. Pipeline fills back up. Repeat. It's #marketmakers.

name: Tim Quast
tweet: $GME, $KOSS both volatility halted 3x the last hour.  Suggests the same reasons caused both.  #marketmakers withdrew, after manufacturing shares -- shorting them -- to fill buy orders.  I think the moment they see limits and stop-losses nearing parity, they exit. @EdgeStructure

name: Tim Quast
tweet: How does $GME keep rising?  Market-makers manufacture shares to fill buy orders, evident in Short Volume near 60%. It's happened each time on the 3-mo run to 1900% gains. And each cycle lasts about ten days.  You can model from @EdgeStructure.  https://t.co/9zxjaO2vlf
